-- Three Top-Managers Leave X5 Following CEO Gusev, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-29T04:32:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-29/three-top-managers-leave-x5-following-ceo-gusev-kommersant-says.html
Three top-managers left Russian food
retailer  X5 Retail Group NV (FIVE)  following the resignation of Chief
Executive Officer Andrey Gusev last month,  Kommersant  reported.  X5’s head of hypermarket format Jan Fuchs, logistics
director Alexander Ermolenko and his deputy Vyacheslav Mekhnenko
left the company, Kommersant said citing X5 statement. The
managers were part of Gusev’s team, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
